    "company": "Regulation: FINRA Rule 4511 / 2025 Regulatory Oversight Report",
    "summary": "FINRA's 2025 Annual Regulatory Oversight Report, published January 28, 2025, explicitly flags firms' failure to retain non-email business communications — including transcripts of video discussions and AI-generated chatbot conversations — as a top compliance gap. FINRA Rule 4511 requires preservation of all business-related communications in WORM-compliant format for six years. The 2025 report specifically calls out 'transcripts of video discussions' as an emerging record type firms are failing to capture. Additionally, FINRA Regulatory Notice 25-07 (April 2025) opens comment on whether video conference transcripts and dynamic website content must be archived. FINRA's 2026 Annual Regulatory Oversight Report flags electronic communications capture failures more than 50 times.",
    "source_url": "https://www.finra.org/rules-guidance/notices/25-07",
    "why_vbrick": "Vbrick's FINRA-ready archiving capabilities — including immutable WORM-compatible video storage, AI-generated transcription with tamper-evident audit trails, and 6-year retention scheduling — directly address FINRA's stated gap. The platform captures video communications, generates searchable transcripts, and integrates with Microsoft Teams (a primary regulated channel), providing a single audit-ready solution across all communication modalities.",
