    "category": "Compliance & Regulatory",
    "company": "Regulation: Section 508 Federal Video Accessibility",
    "summary": "The GSA's third annual Section 508 compliance report confirms that federal agencies continue to fall short of their legal and statutory obligations for accessible ICT, including video. Section 508 requires WCAG 2.0 Level AA compliance for all federal video: accurate synced captions (auto-generated captions are insufficient), audio descriptions for pre-recorded content, accessible video players with keyboard navigation, and descriptive transcripts. Live broadcast video also requires real-time captioning. Federal contractors and recipients of federal funding are bound by these requirements. The NAD v. Harvard/MIT precedent (settled 2019) established video captioning as a fundamental access right.",
    "source_url": "https://www.section508.gov",
    "why_vbrick": "Vbrick's Section 508-compliant video platform delivers AI-powered transcription and captioning that meets WCAG 2.0 Level AA accuracy standards, audio description capabilities, fully keyboard-navigable player controls, and enterprise-grade accessibility reporting for compliance documentation — features absent from commercial video tools used by many federal agencies today.",
    "outreach_angle": "Lead with the GSA report's finding that federal agencies continue to fall short on Section 508 compliance. Ask: 'When was your last Section 508 compliance audit of your video library?' Position Vbrick as the only enterprise video platform purpose-built for Section 508, with AI captioning accuracy that meets WCAG 2.0 AA and audit-ready compliance reporting for every video asset.",
