    "company": "Regulation: EU AI Act High-Risk AI Compliance (August 2026)",
    "summary": "The EU AI Act's high-risk AI system obligations take effect August 2, 2026 (pending proposed amendments that could extend to December 2027, but current law sets the August 2026 date). AI systems used for biometric identification, employment management, or emotion recognition in video are classified as high-risk. Enterprise video platforms using AI transcription, speaker identification, or analytics for employment-related decisions (training assessments, performance monitoring) must implement: risk management systems, technical documentation, human oversight mechanisms, fundamental rights impact assessments (FRIAs), and maintain 6-month automated logs. AI literacy requirements for staff are already in force as of February 2, 2025. GPAI transparency requirements (AI-generated content disclosure) have been in effect since August 2, 2025.",
    "source_url": "https://blog.eprivacy.eu/?p=2329",
