    "company": "Regulation: State Privacy Laws — 2026 New Effective Dates",
    "summary": "As of 2026, 15+ states have active consumer privacy laws with provisions covering biometric and sensitive data. New 2026 effective provisions include: Colorado's biometric data amendments (effective July 1, 2025) requiring employer consent for biometric data collection; Maryland's comprehensive privacy law adding employment context coverage; Kentucky and New Hampshire advancing privacy law amendments through legislatures; New Jersey advancing a bill prohibiting biometric surveillance systems in businesses. Automatic content recognition technology is being added as a category of sensitive data in Kentucky. Enterprise video platforms that use AI analytics for employee monitoring, attendance, or engagement tracking face expanding state-law exposure across the growing patchwork of state regulations.",
